fix(kuma-cp): Stop adding outbounds to dp for vips

The mesh hash contains the vips which now ensures that the watchdog
will regenerate the xds config when needed.

This enables us to remove this extra outbounds in the dataplane resource
and simply generate the outbounds and the dns config in the dataplane_proxy_builder

Users upgrading to this version using transparent proxy in universal will need to reapply all the dps to get rid of the `outbounds` generated previously.

Add TextMarshaler implementations for types that are uses as map keys.
These types are marshaled to JSON for logging, and the map key conversion
in this case requires encoding.TextMarshaler to be implemented. It is
quite confusing for users to see a marshaling error in the Kuma logs,
since it is difficult to distinguish from a real Kuma error.

This fixes #2374.

- Made it consistent with absl::Status
- Removed Status::GetAllPayloads and Status::ReplaceAllPayloads and added Status::ForEachPayload
- Added errors::GetPayloads, errors::InsertPayloads, errors::CopyPayloads, errors::Create and errors::ReplaceMessage

- All old usages updated with the new API
- These changes will unblock codebase-wide update of ensuring payloads are propagated at Status recreation
